[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now Peter and John were going up to the temple at the time"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for prayer,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " at three o’clock in the afternoon."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And a man lame"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from birth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was being carried up, who was placed at the temple gate called “the Beautiful Gate” every day"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so he could beg for money"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from those going into the temple courts."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When he saw Peter and John about to go into the temple courts,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he asked them for money."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Peter looked directly"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " at him (as did John) and said, “Look at us!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So the lame man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " paid attention to them, expecting to receive something from them. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But Peter said, “I have no silver or gold,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but what I do have I give you. In the name"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of Jesus Christ"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the Nazarene, stand up and"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " walk!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Peter"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " took hold"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of him by the right hand and raised him up, and at once the man’s"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " feet and ankles were made strong."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " jumped up,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " stood and began walking around, and he entered the temple courts"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with them, walking and leaping and praising God. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " All"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the people saw him walking and praising God, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and they recognized him as the man who used to sit and ask for donations"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " at the Beautiful Gate of the temple, and they were filled with astonishment and amazement"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " at what had happened to him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " While the man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was hanging on to Peter and John, all the people, completely astounded, ran together to them in the covered walkway"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " called Solomon’s Portico."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When Peter saw this, he declared to the people, “Men of Israel,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " why are you amazed at this? Why"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " do you stare at us as if we had made this man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " walk by our own power or piety? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the God of our forefathers,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has glorified"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his servant"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus, whom you handed over and rejected"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the presence of Pilate after he had decided"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to release him. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But you rejected"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the Holy and Righteous One and asked that a man who was a murderer be released to you. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You killed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the Originator"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of life, whom God raised"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from the dead. To this fact we are witnesses!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And on the basis of faith in Jesus’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " name,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his very name has made this man – whom you see and know – strong. The"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " faith that is through Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has given him this complete health in the presence"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of you all. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And now, brothers, I know you acted in ignorance,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as your rulers did too. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But the things God foretold"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " long ago through"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " all the prophets – that his Christ"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " would suffer – he has fulfilled in this way. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Therefore repent and turn back so that your sins may be wiped out, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so that times of refreshing"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " may come from the presence of the Lord,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and so that he may send the Messiah"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " appointed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for you – that is, Jesus. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " This one"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " heaven must"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " receive until the time all things are restored,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " which God declared"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from times long ago"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " through his holy prophets. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Moses said, ‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "The Lord your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from among your brothers"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ". "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "You must obey"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "him in everything he tells you"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Every person"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "who does not obey that prophet will be destroyed and thus removed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "from the people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And all the prophets, from Samuel and those who followed him, have spoken about and announced"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " these days. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You are the sons of the prophets and of the covenant that God made with your ancestors,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " saying to Abraham, ‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "And in your descendants"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "all the nations"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "of the earth will be blessed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " God raised up"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his servant and sent him first to you, to bless you by turning"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " each one of you from your iniquities.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]